  <note type="source">Smith's Dictionary: "Anaxagoras, a Greek philosopher, was born at Clazomenae
    in Ionia about the year B. C. 499... Anaxagoras explained his dualistic system in a work which
    is now lost, and we know it only from such fragments as are quoted from it by later writers, as
    Plato, Aristotle, Plutarch, Diogenes Laertius, Cicero, and others."</note>
  <note type="source">Clark, G. H. Empedocles and Anaxagoras ... 1929</note>
